@@ -0,0 +1 @@
+Task: review a fixed LaLonde specification-curve analysis. A self-contained R script loads causaldata nsw_mixtape and cps_mixtape, computes the NSW benchmark (1794.34), builds 185 NSW treated plus 15,992 CPS controls, and produces one naive Welch estimate plus eight adjusted cells: covariates {demographics; demographics plus re74/re75} x support {untrimmed; intersection of full-fit treated/control propensity-score ranges} x estimator {fixed-score 1-NN ATT matching with replacement; five treated-score-quintile subclassification}. Scores come from a full-composite main-effects logit. Matching uses MatchIt and pair differences with CR1 clustering by reused original control. Stratification uses treated-count ATT weights and the requested fixed-strata variance. Current computed conclusion is favorable-specification-only recovery: adjusted estimates range -4162 to 1759 versus benchmark 1794; three intervals contain benchmark. Please identify any conceptual or implementation issue that would invalidate this conclusion under the stated contract. Do not edit files.
diff --git a/demos/orchestration-lab/runs/46-sol/vhigh-lalonde/script.R b/demos/orchestration-lab/runs/46-sol/vhigh-lalonde/script.R
